- var workTitle = plist.Presence_in_the_shape.pjTitle;
- var fileName= "Presence_in_the_shape"
- var jpAuthor = "中野 太輔";
- var enAuthor = "Taisuke Nakano"
- var jpDescription = "本作品は，形状変化やスケール変化を行うフレーム構造体に自身の身体を投影させることで，単純な図形にヒトとしての存在感を与えることができないかと考え製作を行ったものである．ヒトの形状をミニマルな図形に落とし込んだ時，それでもそこに個性は生まれるのか，またそこから感情を読み取ることは可能なのか．修士研究において提案・製作を行ってきた，1本のコンベックステープを折り曲げ，それを伸展・収納させることで柔軟な変形を行う構造体'LineShaper'を用いてそれらを提示する．"
- var enDescription = "This work was created with the idea that by projecting my own body onto a frame structure that changes shape and scale, I could give a sense of human presence to a simple figure. When the shape of a human being is incorporated into a minimalist figure, is it still possible to create individuality, and is it possible to read emotions from it? I will present these questions using 'LineShaper,' a structure that flexibly deforms by bending a connexion tape and extending and retracting it, which I proposed and produced in my master's research."

